ebt her brother had left behind. Her reforms and those she made with her husband had an influence that extended well beyond the borders of their united kingdoms. Isabella and Ferdinand are known for completing the Reconquista, ordering conversion or exile of their Muslim and Jewish subjects, and for supporting and financing Christopher Columbus\'s 1492 voyage that led to the opening of the New World and to the establishment of Spain as the first global power which dominated Europe and much of the world for more than a century. Isabella, granted together with her husband the title \"the Catholic\" by Pope Alexander VI, was recognized as a Servant of God by the Catholic Church in 1974.'),('RO0002',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ferdinando',NULL,'Ferdinand II','38SP','King of Aragon',1452,1516,'Isabel','Castilla',NULL,'RO0001','Ferdinand had a role in inaugurating the first European encounters in the future Americas, since he and Isabella sponsored the first voyage of Christopher Columbus (1451–1506), in 1492. That year was the final victory in the war with Granada which defeated the last Muslim state in Iberia and all of Western Europe. This brought to a close the centuries-long Christian reconquest of Iberia. For that Christian victory, Pope Alexander VI, born in the Kingdom of Valencia, awarded the royal couple the title of Catholic Monarchs'),('RO0003',NULL,'RO0004','d\'Aviz',NULL,'Manuele',NULL,'D. Manuel','10PG','Duke of Beja/ King of Portugal',1469,1521,'Maria','Aragon',NULL,'RO0021','Don Manuel I King of Portugal and the Algarves, was the son of Ferdinand, Duke of Viseu, by his wife, the Infanta Beatrice of Portugal'),('RO0004',NULL,NULL,'d\'Aviz',NULL,'Joao',NULL,'D. John II','01PG','King of Portugal',1455,1495,'Eleanor','Viseu',NULL,NULL,'He is known for re-establishing the power of the Portuguese monarchy, reinvigorating the Portuguese economy, and renewing his country\'s exploration of Africa and the Orient'),('RO0005',NULL,'RO0003','d\'Aviz',NULL,'Joao',NULL,'D. John III','01PG','King of Portugal',1502,1557,'Catherine','Austria',NULL,NULL,'During his rule, Portuguese possessions were extended in Asia and in the New World through the Portuguese colonization of Brazil. John III\'s policy of reinforcing Portugal\'s bases in India (such as Goa) secured Portugal\'s monopoly over the spice trade of cloves and nutmeg from the Maluku Islands, as a result of which John III has been called the \"Grocer King\". On the eve of his death in 1557, the Portuguese empire had a global dimension and spanned almost 1 billion acres'),('RO0006',NULL,NULL,'Díaz','Vivar','Rodrigo',NULL,'Rodrigo Díaz de Vivar y Mendoza','34SP','marqués de Cenete',1466,1523,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Problem: Otte transcribs el marques de Cañete but the correct transcription is Cenete. Rodrigo Díaz de Vivar y Mendoza, (c. 1466, Guadalajara – February 22, 1523, Valencia) was a Spanish noble of the House of Mendoza. He was the firstborn son of the powerful Cardinal Pedro González de Mendoza and went on to become the 1st Conde del Cid and the 1st Marquis of Cenete, a title he held from 1491 until his death.'),('RO0007',NULL,NULL,'Sanseverino',NULL,'Roberto',NULL,'Roberto de SanSeverino','03IT','Prince of Salerno',1430,1474,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Roberto II Sanseverino fue hijo de Antonello Sanseverino (1458-1499), gran almirante del Reino de Nápoles y cabecilla de la revuelta antiaragonesa conocida como la Conjura de los barones, y de Costanza di Montefeltro, hija de Federico da Montefeltro, duque de Urbino.'),('RO0008',NULL,NULL,'Fernández','Córdoba','Diego',NULL,'Diego Fernández de Córdoba','01AL','marqués de Comares',1463,1518,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'invested 1st marquis of Comares in 1512, was Governor of Oran and Mazalquivir, 1509–1512 and 1516–1518, and first Viceroy of Navarre, 1512-1515'),('RO0009',NULL,NULL,'Fernández','Córdoba','Pedro',NULL,'Pedro Fernández de Córdoba y Pacheco','04SP','Marques de Priego',1470,1517,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Pedro Fernández de Córdoba y Pacheco 